Enrique Hernandez, Jr.





 
								 
									
								
									Print
								
							
						 










 Director since 2003 Chairman, President and CEO, Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc. Mr. Hernandez has served as the chairman, president and chief executive officer of Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc., a provider of security services located in Pasadena, California, since 1986. Before joining Inter-Con Security Systems in 1984, Mr. Hernandez was a litigation attorney with Brobeck, Phleger & Harrison in Los Angeles. He graduated with honors from Harvard University and went on to attend Harvard Law School, from which he graduated in 1980. Mr. Hernandez is also a director of Chevron Corporation and chairman of the board of McDonald’s Corporation. He is also a member of the board of trustees of the University of Notre Dame, and a member of the Harvard College Visiting and Harvard University Resources Committees and The John Randolph Haynes and Dora Haynes Foundation. Wells Fargo Board Committees: Corporate Responsibility Committee, Finance Committee and Risk Committee






 More Resources  Executive Officers Committees of the Wells Fargo Board Vision and Values   
