Enrique Hernandez Jr.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 3:30 PM ET
Commercial Services and Supplies

Company Overview of Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Enrique   Hernandez Jr.Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President, Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships61--
Background

		Mr. Enrique Hernandez, Jr., also known as Rick, has been the Chief Executive Officer, President and Chairman of Inter-Con Security Systems, Inc. since 1988. Mr. Hernandez is a Co-Founder and has been the Principal Partner of Interspan Communications since 1998. He served as Vice President and Assistant General Counsel of Inter-Con Security Systems Inc. where he joined in 1984 and later served as its Executive Vice President. He served as a litigation attorney with Brobeck, ... Phleger & Harrison, providing general representation of corporate clients and organization and commercial matters. He served as the Non Executive Chairman of Nordstrom Inc. since May 24, 2006 until 2016. He serves as Presiding Director within the meaning of listing standards of the New York Stock Exchange. He serves as a Vice Chairman of Childrens Hospital Los Angeles and Los Angeles County Museum of Art. He serves as Vice Chairman and Director of the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles. He serves as a Trustee of Pomona College and of Notre Dame University. He serves as Trustee of University of Notre Dame. He has been Non Executive Chairman of McDonald's Corporation since May 26, 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Chevron Corporation since December 10, 2008. He has been an Independent Director of McDonald's Corporation since 1996 and Inter-Con Security Systems Inc. since 1984. He served as Presiding Director at Nordstrom Inc until 2016. He has been an Independent Director at Wells Fargo & Company since January 2003. He serves as Director of WMI Holdings Corp. He served as a Lead Director of Nordstrom Inc. from August 2000 to May 22, 2006. He served as an Nordstrom Inc. since 1997 until May 16, 2017. He served as a Director of Washington Mutual Bank. He served as a Director at Wells Fargo & Company since January 2003. He served as a Director of Great Western Financial Corp. since 1993. He served as an Independent Director of Tribune Company since 2001. He serves as Founding Director and Interim Chief Executive Officer of California Healthcare Foundation. He serves as a Board Member of the United States National Infrastructure Advisory Board Committee. He served as the President of the Los Angeles Police Commission from 1993 to 1995. He graduated from Loyola High School, a distinguished Jesuit college preparatory school located in Los Angeles. Subsequent to Loyola, Mr. Hernandez attended Harvard University where he was named a Harvard National Scholar. In 1977, he earned a bachelor's degree in Government and Economics from Harvard College. He received a Juris Doctorate from Harvard Law School in 1980.Read Full Background




